</p>

<p><b>Other Parts Management Systems for hobbiests:</b><br>
<a href="https://inventree.readthedocs.io/">https://inventree.readthedocs.io/</a>&emsp;; based on Python and Dijango. An Open Source well thought out, fully fledged PMS <br>
<a href="https://www.partkeepr.org/">https://www.partkeepr.org/</a>&emsp;; a PHP and composer based Open Source PMS<br>
<a href="https://partsbox.com/">https://partsbox.com/</a>&emsp;; a commercial cloud based PMS, that does allow limited hobby use<br>
<a href="https://bomist.com/">https://bomist.com/</a>&emsp;; a commercial cloud based PMS, with a very limited free use<br>
</p>

<p>More information about the Maker-Hub PMS can be found at the projects website: <br>

<a href="https://github.com/madeinoz67/maker-hub/">https://github.com/madeinoz67/maker-hub/</a></p>
